        <div class="why-cards">
          <div class="why-card">
            <h3><span class="card-icon">‚Üë</span> The Stack Effect</h3>
            <p>As warm air rises and exits your attic, damp crawlspace air is pulled up into your home's living areas.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="why-card">
            <h3><span class="card-icon">~</span> Musty Odors</h3>
            <p>Persistent musty smells inside typically indicate high crawlspace humidity and potential mold growth.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="why-card">
            <h3><span class="card-icon">‚¨°</span> Wood Moisture Concerns</h3>
            <p>Excessive humidity can cause moisture damage and mold growth in subflooring and structural framing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="why-card">
            <h3><span class="card-icon">‚ö°</span> Energy Inefficiency</h3>
            <p>A damp crawlspace increases the load on your HVAC system. Reducing humidity lowers overall moisture and improves efficiency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="why-right">
          <div class="why-image-box">
            <img src="/images/hero-crawlspace.webp" alt="Sealed crawlspace with dehumidifier installed" class="why-photo" />
          </div>
          <div class="why-summary">
            <h3>Why Humidity Control Matters</h3>
            <p class="summary-sub">Proper crawlspace humidity control is essential for a healthy home environment.</p>
            <ul class="summary-list">
              <li><span class="check">&#10004;</span> Prevent wood rot, mold, and musty odors</li>
              <li><span class="check">&#10004;</span> Improve indoor air quality throughout your home</li>
              <li><span class="check">&#10004;</span> Increase HVAC efficiency and lower energy bills</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-green">Request Inspection</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

